# Day 7: Back from vacation and boy is the level design hard
###### 24.04.2023

Back from my short trip and jumping back into the development! Since the goal of the last session was to equip a weapon, and it failed, I decided to get it done today. And voila:

![]({{site.url}}images/7.1.png)

I decided not to circumvent the complicated Intentory system of the FCS, but instead to make it as minimal as I can to just equip the weapon I want. So now in the beginning of every game session, I need to pick up a sword from the ground and equip it - but its good enough for now.

To take a small break from the logic part, I thought it might be fun and relaxing to try creating a prototype level I had in mind. I had sketched something already and was very excited to try it out with the amazing free Dungeon asset pack, but boy was I wrong about it being relaxing. I don't even feel like going into many details of how many things can go wrong, so after a while of struggling, I have decided to focus up my efforts elsewhere for now. In order to do proper level design, I need to come to this fresh and look through some tutorials, from lighting to landscape stuff.

Anyhow, here's another screenshot, this time of the demonstration level of the asset pack. Looks cool af not gonna lie.

